"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789978","HM Treasury","false","2017-11-21","<p>The future of our relationship with the European Supervisory Authorities is subject to the outcome of the withdrawal negotiations. The UK and the EU will start from the unique position of regulatory alignment. We will look to create a new framework that allows for continued trust in one another’s institutions and a close partnership.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789978/answer",,,,,"113252","2017-11-21T14:15:51.547Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789978/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/789978/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-11-15","European Securities and Markets Authority","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether the Government plans to seek formal agreement to participate in the European Securities and Markets Authority after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Stephen Kinnock","Aberavon","Stephen Kinnock","113250"
