"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/790122","Home Office","false","2017-11-20","<p>Data on the timeliness of responses to hon. Members is published by UK Visas and Immigration as part of the quarterly transparency data. The most recent data can be found here -</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/customer-service-operations-data-august-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/customer-service-operations-data-august-2017</a></p><p> </p><p>UKVI does not publish data in the four, eight and ten week format requested.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/790122/answer",,,,,,"2017-11-20T17:56:20.867Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/790122/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/790122/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-11-15","UK Visas and Immigration: Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what proportion of UK Visas and Immigration enquiries received from hon. Members have been answered within (a) four, (b) eight and (c) 10 weeks in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Vicky Foxcroft","Lewisham, Deptford","Vicky Foxcroft","113393"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/790123","Home Office","false","2017-11-20","<p>UKVI has seen an unprecedented increase in the levels of enquiries from Hon Members since July, leading to a decline in timeliness of some responses. UKVI has deployed further resource to meet intake and assist in returning to previous levels of service.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/790123/answer",,,,,,"2017-11-20T17:55:57.79Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/790123/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/790123/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-11-15","UK Visas and Immigration: Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what assessment she has made of the adequacy of the timeliness of responses by UK Visas and Immigration to hon. Members' enquiries.","false","Biography information for Vicky Foxcroft","Lewisham, Deptford","Vicky Foxcroft","113394"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/790124","Home Office","false","2017-11-20","<p>Published data on UKVI’s performance against service standards for applications made in the UK and from overseas, including the proportion of cases classified as non-straightforward, can be found here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/migration-transparency-data%23uk-visas-and-immigration" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/migration-transparency-data#uk-visas-and-immigration</a>.</p><p> </p><p>Where an application is defined as non-straightforward due to complexity, the customer will be written to within the normal processing time to explain why it will not be decided within the normal standard, and to explain what will happen next.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/790124/answer",,,,,,"2017-11-20T17:59:57.2Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/790124/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/790124/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-11-15","Immigration: Applications","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what proportion of immigration applications have been completed within the service standard limit in (a) 2016 and (b) 2017.","false","Biography information for Vicky Foxcroft","Lewisham, Deptford","Vicky Foxcroft","113395"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/790125","Home Office","false","2017-11-21","<p>The government expects Chief Constables (individually and through the National Police Chiefs Council) and PCCs to take HMICFRS inspection findings very seriously and to implement any recommendations made. The report on “Stolen Freedoms” did not make any recommendations for the government to take forward.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/790125/answer",,,,,,"2017-11-21T17:34:36.537Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/790125/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/790125/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-11-15","Slavery","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what plans she has to respond to the report entitled Stolen Freedom, published in October 2017 by Her Majesty's Inspector of Constabulary.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","113359"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/790126","Home Office","false","2017-11-20","<p>The association between the consumption of cheap, super-strength beers and ciders and anti-social behaviour and low level crime is well known. The Government has set out its approach to reducing alcohol-related crime and disorder in the Modern Crime Prevention Strategy, published in 2016.</p><p>Alcohol-related violent incidents, as measured by the Crime Survey for England and Wales, has fallen from 901,000 in 2009/10 to 491,000 in 2015/16; the proportion of people reporting drunk or rowdy behaviour as a problem in their neighbourhood has also fallen, from 24% in 2009/10 to 16% in 2016/17.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/790126/answer",,,,,,"2017-11-20T17:36:05.127Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/790126/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/790126/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-11-15","Alcoholic Drinks: Crime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what assessment she has made of the impact of cheap, super-strength alcohol on levels of crime and antisocial behaviour.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","113328"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/790127","Home Office","false","2017-11-21","<p>We are considering the options for our future immigration system very carefully and we will be setting out initial proposals for our future immigration arrangements in due course.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/790127/answer",,,,,,"2017-11-21T17:23:27.407Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/790127/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/790127/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-11-15","Immigration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, when her Department intends to publish a White Paper on immigration.","false","Biography information for Sue Hayman","Workington","Sue Hayman","113261"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/790128","Home Office","false","2017-11-21","<p>For the time being, the United Kingdom remains a part of the European Union and the latest labour market statistics continue to show an increased number of EU citizens entering into the UK labour force. However, the Government has committed to keeping the position under review and we will continue to engage with the agricultural sector.</p><p>The Government has commissioned the Migration Advisory Committee (MAC) to assess the impact of leaving the EU and the subsequent needs of the UK economy, including the rural economy. We will outline our future immigration proposals in due course.</p><p>Net migration includes all persons coming to the UK for 12 months or longer.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/790128/answer",,,,,"113263 ; 113364","2017-11-21T17:25:18.797Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/790128/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/790128/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-11-15","Agriculture: Seasonal Workers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if her Department will introduce a trial seasonal agricultural workers scheme in 2018.","false","Biography information for Sue Hayman","Workington","Sue Hayman","113262"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/790129","Home Office","false","2017-11-21","<p>For the time being, the United Kingdom remains a part of the European Union and the latest labour market statistics continue to show an increased number of EU citizens entering into the UK labour force. However, the Government has committed to keeping the position under review and we will continue to engage with the agricultural sector.</p><p>The Government has commissioned the Migration Advisory Committee (MAC) to assess the impact of leaving the EU and the subsequent needs of the UK economy, including the rural economy. We will outline our future immigration proposals in due course.</p><p>Net migration includes all persons coming to the UK for 12 months or longer.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/790129/answer",,,,,"113262 ; 113364","2017-11-21T17:25:18.86Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/790129/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/790129/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-11-15","Rural Areas: Migrant Workers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps her Department is taking to ensure that rural businesses are able to recruit the workers they require from countries within the EU and elsewhere.","false","Biography information for Sue Hayman","Workington","Sue Hayman","113263"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/790130","Home Office","false","2017-12-04","<p>Her Majesty’s Passport Office does not record the number of complaints received that relate to the delivery of a UK passport by any further subset. It is therefore not possible to identify the number of complaints that have been made in relation to DX’s contract to deliver UK passports.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/790130/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-04T17:12:58.997Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/790130/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/790130/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-11-15","Passports: Postal Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many complaints her Department has received on the performance of the courier company DX in relation to its contract to deliver UK passports on behalf of the Passport Office in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","113344"
